3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of attention-based decoders and transition-based parsers in the models. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for text generation. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category as the paper does not primarily focus on software engineering, but it does involve the development of a new model for text generation.
